Lecture Tips

Dataviz tips: * 3D is bad, make sure the color is distinguished from the each other; * Never use the pie chart; * Use Color to highlight groups; * Do use the Common Axes; * Good figures are not necessarily the publication quality pictures; Why ggplot: * “Relative” is compared with the base R graphics; * Much easier and much more convinient; * Learning curve for ggplot2/lattice(another package) is needed; learning ggplot: * Stackoverflow; Using ggplot: * data tidy issue is linked affects the ability to visualize

gg = grammar of graphics Basic graph components: * data * aesthetic mappings * geoms

Advanced graph components: facets scales *statistics

A graph is built by combining these components

Git repo for visualizing the data

  • the t means temp and is measured in celsuis degree.

#start a plot

ggplot(weather_df, aes(x = tmin, y = tmax)) + 
  geom_point()
## Warning: Removed 15 rows containing missing values (geom_point).

* you can pipe directly and don’t need to sepcify about the data name

weather_df %>% 
  filter(name == "CentralPark_NY") %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = tmin, y = tmax)) %>% +
  geom_point()

## More Plot options

plot_weather = 
  weather_df %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = tmin, y = tmax)) 

plot_weather + geom_point()
## Warning: Removed 15 rows containing missing values (geom_point).

ggplot(weather_df, aes(x = tmin, y = tmax)) + 
  geom_point(aes(color = name))
## Warning: Removed 15 rows containing missing values (geom_point).

## Add a geom _line for the graph

ggplot(weather_df, aes(x = tmin, y = tmax)) + 
  geom_point(aes(color = name), alpha = .5) +
  geom_smooth(se = FALSE)
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'gam' and formula 'y ~ s(x, bs = "cs")'
## Warning: Removed 15 rows containing non-finite values (stat_smooth).
## Warning: Removed 15 rows containing missing values (geom_point).

geom_smooth()
## geom_smooth: na.rm = FALSE, se = TRUE
## stat_smooth: na.rm = FALSE, se = TRUE, method = auto, formula = y ~ x
## position_identity
  • alpha blending level - transparent/ not transparent
ggplot(weather_df, aes(x = tmin, y = tmax)) + 
  geom_point(aes(color = name), alpha = .2) +
  geom_smooth(se = FALSE)
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'gam' and formula 'y ~ s(x, bs = "cs")'
## Warning: Removed 15 rows containing non-finite values (stat_smooth).

* Create every line not a global line

ggplot(weather_df, aes(x = tmin, y = tmax)) + 
  geom_point(aes(color = name), alpha = .1) +
  geom_smooth(aes(color = name),se = FALSE)
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula 'y ~ x'
## Warning: Removed 15 rows containing non-finite values (stat_smooth).
## Warning: Removed 15 rows containing missing values (geom_point).

Facetting…

ggplot(weather_df, aes(x = tmin, y = tmax)) + 
  geom_point(aes(color = name), alpha = .1) +
  geom_smooth(aes(color = name), se = FALSE) +
 facet_grid(~ name)
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula 'y ~ x'
## Warning: Removed 15 rows containing non-finite values (stat_smooth).
## Warning: Removed 15 rows containing missing values (geom_point).

A more interesting plot / use the date as x.

ggplot(weather_df, aes(x = date, y= tmax, color = name, size = prcp)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(se = FALSE)+
  facet_grid(~ name)
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula 'y ~ x'
## Warning: Removed 3 rows containing non-finite values (stat_smooth).
## Warning: Removed 3 rows containing missing values (geom_point).

Hist in smooth

ggplot(weather_df, aes(x = tmax, fill = name)) +
  geom_density(alpha = .5)
## Warning: Removed 3 rows containing non-finite values (stat_density).

Boxplots!!

ggplot(weather_df, aes(x = tmax, y =tmax, fill = name)) +
  geom_boxplot(alpha = .5) 
## Warning: Removed 3 rows containing missing values (stat_boxplot).

  • violin plots for group comparison
ggplot(weather_df, aes(x = tmin, y = tmax, fill = name)) +
  geom_violin(alpha = .5) 
## Warning: Removed 15 rows containing non-finite values (stat_ydensity).
## Warning: position_dodge requires non-overlapping x intervals

ridges plot

ggplot(weather_df, aes(x = tmax, y = name)) + 
  geom_density_ridges(scale = .85)
## Picking joint bandwidth of 1.84
## Warning: Removed 3 rows containing non-finite values (stat_density_ridges).

## gg save for saving the document

weather_plot = ggplot(weather_df, aes(x = tmax, y = name)) + 
  geom_density_ridges(scale = .85)
ggsave("weather plot.png", weather_plot, width = 8, height = 5)
## Picking joint bandwidth of 1.84
## Warning: Removed 3 rows containing non-finite values (stat_density_ridges).
